Currently, the University boasts a bandwidth of 
over 950 Mbps, with the following key 
infrastructure and services: 
• Data Centre: NED University has revolutionised 
its network and data services by establishing a 
state-of-the-art Data Centre comprising five 
server racks and four network racks. The 
primary objective is to provide efficient and 
high-standard services. 
• FO LAN: A state-of-the-art optical fibre LAN 
connecting every facility within the University. 
• Broadband 
Connectivity: 
Robust, 
high-
bandwidth connectivity for all users (up to 8 
Mbps). 
• Smart University: HEC Smart University 
campus-wide Wi-Fi provides secure broadband 
connectivity to students, faculty, and staff 
across the Main Campus, LEJ Campus, and City 
Campus. 
• Inter-Campus 
Connectivity: 
All 
remote 
campuses (LEJ, City) and the constituent college 
TIEST are connected via VPN to the Main 
Campus, ensuring full access to Extranet and 
Intranet facilities. 
• NEDUET 
VPN: 
Secure 
VPN 
access 
for 
researchers and students, enabling access to 
the HEC Digital Library and NEDUET Portal 
services.  
7.2.2  Online Learning Management System 
Pioneering 
online 
higher 
education, 
NED 
University has not only transformed its teaching 
mechanisms for online delivery but also 
contributed significantly to developing national-
level online teaching strategies through the 
Higher Education Commission (HEC). 
During the pandemic, the University turned 
challenges into opportunities by re-engineering its 
educational systems and policies to meet the 
demands of online distance learning. Through the 
NEDUET Learning Management System (LMS)—
integrating G Suite, NED Portal, NED VPN, etc.—
the University implemented a comprehensive 
plan encompassing technology deployment, 
faculty training, and quality digital content 
development. 
This was complemented by modified examination 
policies, ensuring quality education, effective 
student participation, and measurable academic 
outcomes.  
7.2.3 Hardware Maintenance and Inventory  
The Department provides both hardware and 
software support services, in addition to 
managing hardware inventory and conducting 
technical feasibility assessments.  
7.2.4 Video Conferencing Facility 
The University houses a centrally located Video 
Conferencing Facility Centre, enabling NEDUET to 
connect globally for virtual classes, conferences, 
seminars, and meetings. This facility supports 
multi-location video and voice communication 
and is available around the clock.  
7.2.5 Information Systems and Software Section 
The IT Department is committed to delivering 
state-of-the-art software solutions using Agile 
Methodology for faster development with 
uncompromising quality and integrity. Some of 
the key systems developed include: 
• 
Undergraduate and Postgraduate Students 
Management System 
• 
Human Resource Management System 
• 
Attendance Information System 
• 
Shuttle Pass System 
• 
Hostel Management System 
• 
LTV Management System 
• 
Security Operations Management System 
• 
Statutory Bodies Management System 
• 
Academic Performance Monitoring System 
• 
Scholarships Management System 
• 
Internship Management System 
In addition to Management Information Systems 
(MIS), several web-based applications have been 
developed by the Department to automate core 
University processes, such as online semester 
registration (undergraduate and postgraduate), 
online feedback collection, and online admissions. 
This 
comprehensive 
and 
sophisticated 
development effort is collectively known as the 
NEDUET 
Campus 
Management 
System 
(NEDUET-CMS). Access to the CMS is provided via 
the NEDUET Campus Portal, a 24/7 service 
featuring single sign-on for multiple applications, 
with personalised, secure, and role-based access. 
Portal Features for Undergraduate Students: 
• 
Personal and Academic Profile 
• 
Subject-wise up-to-date Attendance 
Status 
• 
Class and Examination Schedules 
• 
Announcements from Course Teachers 
• 
Access to Study Material uploaded by 
Course Teachers 
• 
Personal Letters issued by the Registrar’s 
Office 
• 
Notice Board for official notifications and 
announcements 
• 
Internship application, tracking, and 
withdrawal 
• 
Semester registration details for regular 
and backlog courses 
• 
Online course and teacher feedback
