Creating a dynamic and productive ecosystem for 
knowledge exchange and innovation, The Directorate of 
Industrial Liaison (DIL) aims to develop and strengthen 
essential industry-university linkages through a variety 
of activities, including: 
Industrial Visits: Organizing study visits to various 
organizations for students and faculty, providing them 
with real-world experience. 
Internships & Co-op Education Programme: Assisting in 
arranging internship opportunities during vacations for 
students across different industries. Additionally, DIL 
also invites the industry to collaborate with NED’s 
“Cooperative Education (Co-op) Programme”, and to 
consider accepting NED students as interns throughout 
their academic journey, from the first year to the final 
year, with the possibility of continued placement based 
on performance, especially during students' vacations. 
Final Year Design Projects (FYDPs): Facilitating the 
collection of FYDPs from the industry and organizing 
technical and practical support from the industries 
involved in these projects. 
Job Placement: Supporting employers with job 
placement through various channels, including on-
campus recruitment drives, website job postings, 
graduate directories, and Career Fairs. 
Mentorship/Career Counseling: Facilitating mentoring 
and career counseling sessions for students. 
Exhibitions: Encouraging students to present their work 
at professional fairs, expos, and shows. 
Faculty Industrial Placement Programme (FIPP): DIL 
cordially invites industries to consider taking part in our 
FIPP. Faculty members of NED may be able to spend 
their two to three-month vacation time embedded in 
the industry through this programme. This firsthand 
experience not only enriches faculty’s teaching 
methodologies but also enables them to better prepare 
our students for the demands of the ever-evolving job 
market. Other Industrial Collaboration: Facilitating 
collaboration through NED's expertise in industrial 
training, lab testing, consultancies, and R&D efforts. 
Website: https://www.neduet.edu.pk/DIL 
