facilities_info_chunk_0	facilities_info	Facilities Info	NED UNIVERSITY - FACILITIES ============================ 1. ENGR. ABUL KALAM LIBRARY ---------------------------- Established in 1921, one of Pakistan's leading academic libraries focusing on engineering sciences and technology. Serves as the regional reference library of engineering and technology. Library Collection: - General circulation books (textbooks) - Reference books (encyclopedias, handbooks, dictionaries, manuals) - Periodicals (current subscriptions + previous journal volumes) - Government documents & archive material (Acts, Ordinances, Service Rules, Statistical reports, Census reports) - Survey reports, Planning reports, Budgets - Audio Visual content (CDROMs, DVDs) - Digital content (eBooks, eJournals) Security: - State-of-the-art RFID-based security system Department Libraries: - Located at City Campus, LEJ Campus, and Main Campus - NED Academy library for CCEE and CMPP students Book Bank Service (Undergraduates): - Textbooks provided at 10% of cost for the entire semester Lending Library / Duty Society (Undergraduates): - Textbooks provided free of cost for the entire semester Technology: - Computerised Library Management System, Website, OPAC, Portal - 65 latest-configuration computers - Digital services: e-Books, e-Journals (HEC National Digital Library), laser printing, scanning, CD/DVD writing, copying Mission: User-oriented learning environment, preserve universal knowledge. 2. INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (IT) SERVICES ---------------------------------------- Established: 1998-99 NEDUET Campus Management System (CMS): - Paperless environment for admin
facilities_info_chunk_1	facilities_info	Facilities Info	printing, scanning, CD/DVD writing, copying Mission: User-oriented learning environment, preserve universal knowledge. 2. INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (IT) SERVICES ---------------------------------------- Established: 1998-99 NEDUET Campus Management System (CMS): - Paperless environment for admin & academic departments - Systems: Undergraduate/PG Student Management, HR Management, Attendance, Security Operations, Academic Performance Monitoring - Journal and research databanks - Single sign-on 24/7 portal (NEDUET Campus Portal) - Online semester registration for UG & PG students NEDUET Website: - Dedicated Web Development Team - Supports departmental websites Metro LAN: - First in educational public sector - 37 km Optical Fibre Metro Area Network (MAN) - Connects Main, LEJ & City Campuses NEDUET ISP: - 24x7 high-speed Internet access - Dial-up service available - Network Operation Centre (NOC) with enterprise-grade equipment NEDUET WiFi: - Campus-wide coverage via iAccess captive portal - Authentication, accounting services Video Conferencing: - Centrally-located facility for virtual classes, conferences, seminars - Available 24/7, local and international connectivity Computational Services (HPC): - First public sector university in Pakistan to build own clusters - Two HPC clusters: - 50 nodes (32-bit architecture) - 32 virtualised nodes (64-bit architecture) - Accessible from all campuses + remotely via internet Software Repository: - Generic and application-oriented licensed software - Standalone:
facilities_info_chunk_2	facilities_info	Facilities Info	- 50 nodes (32-bit architecture) - 32 virtualised nodes (64-bit architecture) - Accessible from all campuses + remotely via internet Software Repository: - Generic and application-oriented licensed software - Standalone: HPC Centre only | Network-based: entire university Training: - Trainings, seminars, workshops for staff, faculty, and students IT Help Desk: - Software & Desktop Support - Network Support - Hardware Maintenance - NEDUET-CMS (Portal) - High Performance Computing (HPC) - Services extended to all three campuses 3. INSTRUMENTATION CENTRE -------------------------- Established under HEC grant. Provides testing & calibration services. Capabilities: - Calibration of multimeters, energy meters, pressure/temperature gauges, water quality, flow - Training for UG and PG students - Assists final year projects and R&D activities Laboratories: - Electronics and Signals Lab - Pressure and Temperature Lab - Equipment Testing Lab - Water Quality and Flow Testing Lab - Virtual Instrumentation Lab (National Instruments LabVIEW) Accreditation: - Pursuing ISO 17025 accreditation - Goal: Regional leader in test & calibration - Will provide services to industries/organisations in Karachi area 4. NED ACADEMY --------------- Established: 1 July 2008 (CCEE founded 1998) Objectives: - Update engineers with recent developments - Enhance employability of working engineers - Help lower-tier professionals meet registration levels -
facilities_info_chunk_3	facilities_info	Facilities Info	ACADEMY --------------- Established: 1 July 2008 (CCEE founded 1998) Objectives: - Update engineers with recent developments - Enhance employability of working engineers - Help lower-tier professionals meet registration levels - Structured programmes for engineers unable to pursue formal Masters - Postgraduate diplomas in specific technologies (sugar, plastics, etc.) Two Sections: - Centre for Continuing Engineering Education (CCEE) - University-Industry partnerships, continuing education courses - Centre for Multidisciplinary Postgraduate Programmes (CMPP) - Long-duration certificate courses, PG Certificate Courses 5. FERROCEMENT INTERNATIONAL NETWORK (FIN-PAKISTAN) ---------------------------------------------------- - National Node for ferrocement, established 1990 in Civil Engineering Dept. - Under International Node at IFIC-AIT-BANGKOK - Disburses research material and disseminates knowledge in ferrocement 6. COWASJEE EARTHQUAKE STUDY CENTRE (CESNED) ---------------------------------------------- - Established 2001 after Bhuj earthquake - Under Department of Earthquake Engineering - Houses national & global earthquake data - Disseminates earthquake knowledge - Responds to emergency needs - Guiding principles for pre/post disaster mitigation - Recognised as one of two earthquake study centres in Pakistan (after 2005 Kashmir earthquake) 7. SHAKE TABLE TESTING FACILITY --------------------------------- - State-of-the-art facility in Earthquake Engineering Department - Simulates real-time earthquake ground motion - Records dynamic response of structures 8. ADVANCED MATERIAL TESTING FACILITY -------------------------------------- - State-of-the-art facility
facilities_info_chunk_4	facilities_info	Facilities Info	FACILITY --------------------------------- - State-of-the-art facility in Earthquake Engineering Department - Simulates real-time earthquake ground motion - Records dynamic response of structures 8. ADVANCED MATERIAL TESTING FACILITY -------------------------------------- - State-of-the-art facility in Earthquake Engineering Department - Full-scale static and pseudo-dynamic testing - Tests structural components of buildings and bridges 9. PCB FABRICATION LABORATORY ------------------------------- - Located in Electronic Engineering Department - Trains UG students in PCB fabrication technology - Supported by PCB layout design and auto-routing software - Fabricates PCBs for local requirements 10. PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT CENTRE (PDC) ------------------------------------- - Fully equipped with sophisticated equipment and software - Used for re-engineering 11. DIRECTORATE OF INDUSTRIAL LIAISON (DIL) -------------------------------------------- Established: 1997 Activities: - Arranges internship opportunities for students - Collects suggestions for Final Year Design Project topics - Arranges technical/practical help from industries - Industry-assigned projects with advisors - Study visits for students and faculty 12. MEDICAL DEPARTMENT ----------------------- Staff: - 6 doctors total - Main Campus: 2 morning, 1 evening - LEJ Campus: 1 - City Campus: 1 lady doctor - Headed by Principal Medical Officer - Paramedical staff (male & female nurses) Facilities (free for students at Main Campus): - Emergency and Outpatient services - Pathological, Radiological, ECG labs -
facilities_info_chunk_5	facilities_info	Facilities Info	Headed by Principal Medical Officer - Paramedical staff (male & female nurses) Facilities (free for students at Main Campus): - Emergency and Outpatient services - Pathological, Radiological, ECG labs - Airway, breathing, circulatory intervention - X-Ray, Pathology Lab, Ambulance (Main Campus only) - Outpatient at City and LEJ Campus 13. OTHER STUDENT FACILITIES ----------------------------- Duty Society: - Interest-free loans for students in financial need - Apply through Secretary of the Society Book Bank: - Textbooks issued at nominal charges for one academic year - Books returned at end of academic year Plain Paper Copiers (PPC): - Document copying at nominal cost Stationery Shop: - University General Store on campus - No-profit basis, managed by teaching staff committee Sports Facilities: - Athletics, Badminton, Cricket, Football, Table Tennis, Hockey, Physical Fitness, Basketball Hostel (Muhammad Bin Qasim Hostel): - Adjacent to campus - Common Room, Prayer Hall, Warden's Office & Room - For non-residents of Karachi - Application form from National Bank of Pakistan or Habib Metropolitan Bank (NED Branch) - Fresh entrants apply after admission selection Boys' Common Room: - Indoor games, telephone, reading material Girls' Common Room: - Furnished, attached bath/powder room, maid servant Transport: - Shuttle bus from convenient points
facilities_info_chunk_6	facilities_info	Facilities Info	apply after admission selection Boys' Common Room: - Indoor games, telephone, reading material Girls' Common Room: - Furnished, attached bath/powder room, maid servant Transport: - Shuttle bus from convenient points - Places and charges notified by the University
FAQ_extracted_chunk_0	FAQ_extracted	Faq	Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) UNDERGRADUATE ADMISSIONS Admission form Q1. How can I get Admission Form? A. Application for the Undergraduate Admissions is available at Admission Web Portal www.neduet.edu.pk/admission. Q2. Who is eligible to apply for Admission? A. An applicant who is appearing in HSC-II or Equivalent Examination in 2026 and have passed his/her previous examination. An applicant who has passed HSC-II or Equivalent Examination in 2025, 2024 or 2023. Q3. What is the minimum percentage in HSC or Equivalent Examinations required for the admission to undergraduate programmes? A. For all Bachelors of Engineering Programmes, Bachelor of Architecture and BS (Computer Science) minimum 60% in HSC or Equivalent Examinations is required but candidates who have secured at least 57% in HSC-1 or Equivalent Examinations (O-Levels for Cambridge Examination Board) are eligible to apply. However, they must maintain a minimum of 60% in their HSC/Equivalent examinations to confirm their admission. For all BS Programmes except BS (Computer Science) minimum 50% in HSC or Equivalent Examinations is required. Please see Chapter-4 of the Undergraduate Prospectus for details. Following table illustrates the summary: Candidates having passed /appeared in HSC with following Subjects Degree Programmes Eligible for Application 60% or above 50% or above HSC
FAQ_extracted_chunk_1	FAQ_extracted	Faq	Undergraduate Prospectus for details. Following table illustrates the summary: Candidates having passed /appeared in HSC with following Subjects Degree Programmes Eligible for Application 60% or above 50% or above HSC (Pre-Engineering/ Equivalent) (Maths/ Physics/ Chemistry) All Undergraduate Programmes All BS Programmes except BS (Computer Science) HSC (Pre-Medical/ Equivalent) (Biology/ Physics/Chemistry) Biomedical Engineering, BS (Computer Science), B. Arch Programme and all BS Programmes except BS (Computational Finance). All BS Programmes except BS (Computer Science) and BS (Computational Finance) HSC (Computer Science/ • All BE Programmes subject to BS Management Sciences, Equivalent) register and qualifying an additional BS Development Studies, (Mathematics/ Physics/ Computer Sc.) Non-Credit (NC) Course of Chemistry, BS Computational Finance, that will be offered by the University BS English Linguistics, during First year Fall semester. BS Economics & Finance University will charge an additional fee BS Physics, BS English and for this NC course. BS Textile Sciences. • BS Computer Science, Management Sciences, Development Studies, English Linguistics, English, Computational Finance, Economics & Finance, Textile Sciences, Physics, English and Bachelor of Architecture without having study any additional Course. HSC (Computer Science/ BS (Computer Science), Development Studies, Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Economics & Finance, Computational Finance. BS in Development Equivalent) Studies,
FAQ_extracted_chunk_2	FAQ_extracted	Faq	Architecture without having study any additional Course. HSC (Computer Science/ BS (Computer Science), Development Studies, Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Economics & Finance, Computational Finance. BS in Development Equivalent) Studies, (Maths, Statistics, Computer Sc.) Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Economics & Finance, Computational Finance. HSC (Arts (Mathematics)) HSC examination with Mathematics, in addition to other prescribed subjects. The applicant must also have passed IGCSE/GCE ‘O’ Levels or SSC examinations with the Science Group. BS (Computer Science), Development Studies, Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Economics & Finance, Computational Finance. BS in Development Studies, Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Economics & Finance, Computational Finance. HSC (Commerce/ Equivalent) BS in Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Development Studies, Economics & Finance. BS in Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Development Studies, Economics & Finance. HSC (Arts/ Equivalent) BS in Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Development Studies, Economics & Finance. BS in Management Sciences, English Linguistics, English, Development Studies, Economics & Finance. Candidates having /appeared in HSC with following Subjects Degree Programmes Eligible for Application 60% or above 50% or above Candidates having BE Civil Not applicable for DAE. passed DAE (in relevant BE Civil (with specialization in field) from Urban Engineering), Sindh Board of BE
FAQ_extracted_chunk_3	FAQ_extracted	Faq	or above 50% or above Candidates having BE Civil Not applicable for DAE. passed DAE (in relevant BE Civil (with specialization in field) from Urban Engineering), Sindh Board of BE Petroleum, Technical Education BE Mechanical, (SBTE) BE Textile BE Industrial & Manufacturing BE Automotive BE Electrical, BE Telecommunication, BE Electronics, BE Chemical, BE Metallurgical, BE Materials BE Polymer & Petrochemical Note: Admissions are purely based on Merit. Q4. What is the merit criteria for merit for admission in undergraduate programmes? A. The overall merit in respect of candidates from admission shall be determined based on Merit Score (MS) to be calculated as: MS = 40% (HSC Part I/ O-level Marks/ Equivalent Examinations) * + 60% (NED Entry Test Marks) * For candidates already completed HSC/A-level/Equivalent examinations will be dealt as per policy. Q5. How should I take an additional Non-Credit (NC) course based on my admitted program and my intermediate/equivalent group? A. The University will offer an additional NC course in First year, Fall semester, and students must qualify this course. The University will charge an additional fee for this NC course. Q6. I have been appearing in additional mathematics/improvement examinations, which marks/year I have to enter in the admission
FAQ_extracted_chunk_4	FAQ_extracted	Faq	course. The University will charge an additional fee for this NC course. Q6. I have been appearing in additional mathematics/improvement examinations, which marks/year I have to enter in the admission form? A. You have to enter the HSC/Equivalent examination marks/year which you have completed or for which you have the complete result in hand by the last date of online submission of admission application. Q7. What to do, if I am unable to register on Admission Web Portal? or email address is already registered? Or User Name and Password not received via email? A. You have to re-check that either you have already registered with the same email address or CNIC number. If you did not receive the login information, please check Junk or Spam folder in your email. In both cases, please contact on Helpdesk to resolve the issue. Q8. What to do, if I am unable to login to the Admission Portal with the provided User ID and Password? A. Make sure to enter the correct User ID and Password, since the password is case sensitive. Also make sure the difference between “0” (zero) and “O” (O for orange), “L” (L for Leaf) or “I” (I for Ink)
FAQ_extracted_chunk_5	FAQ_extracted	Faq	and Password, since the password is case sensitive. Also make sure the difference between “0” (zero) and “O” (O for orange), “L” (L for Leaf) or “I” (I for Ink) which usually cause password error. Q9. What if, I am unable to upload my photograph on the Admission Portal? A. Please make sure that your photograph is according to the instructions provided in “Guideline for the Application Photograph”. Q10. How can I pay Application Fee? A. Following procedure is to be followed for the payment of the application fee: i) After completing Online Application Form, required application fee (including self- finance/sponsor fee, if applicable) shall be indicated on the Transaction Slip, which contains an important number called Transaction ID. ii) Take a Print-out of Transaction Slip and pay the indicated fee at any branch of the banks specified on Transaction Slip. iii) It is very important to note that the payment at the bank should be against the Transaction ID mentioned on the Transaction Slip. Q11. How would I get my Pre-Admission Entry Test ADMIT CARD? A. After confirmation of receipt of fee at the bank, ADMIT CARD will be available in the Online Admission Portal, provided all other requirements
FAQ_extracted_chunk_6	FAQ_extracted	Faq	my Pre-Admission Entry Test ADMIT CARD? A. After confirmation of receipt of fee at the bank, ADMIT CARD will be available in the Online Admission Portal, provided all other requirements (mainly photograph) found suitable. Please note that Admit Card will be not issued if either the fee payment is not confirmed or uploaded photograph is invalid. Q12. What to do after passing Pre-Admission Entry Test? A. You are required to follow the admission schedule and instructions given on it. For updates kindly refer to NED University website: https://www.neduet.edu.pk/admission. Q13. Where Admission Form can be submitted? A. You need to print out the Admission Form along with Annexures (I & II), duly signed from Oath Commissioner and submit with other required documents to Admission Office of the University at the time of interview. Please refer the Document Checklist for further details. Q14. How can I apply for any additional category? A. You can apply against any additional category for which you are eligible during initial submission of online Admission Form, latest by the due date. Note: Eligibility for admission under each category/discipline is as described in Chapter-4 & Chapter-5 of the Undergraduate Prospectus (Soft copy is available at NED University website).
FAQ_extracted_chunk_7	FAQ_extracted	Faq	by the due date. Note: Eligibility for admission under each category/discipline is as described in Chapter-4 & Chapter-5 of the Undergraduate Prospectus (Soft copy is available at NED University website). Q15. Do I have to pay any fee for Additional category? A. No, there is NO extra fee for additional category(ies) in which you are eligible to apply except Self-Finance category(ies). Q16. What are the requirements of admission in the category of differently able candidate? A. For admission in category for those having disability and passed HSC (Pre- Engineering/Pre-Medical/Computer Science/Arts/Arts-Math/Commerce) part I and II (as the case may be), from any Board of Intermediate of Education situated in province of Sindh and having certificate of disability from Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities (DEPD), Government of Sindh. Further the candidate is required to appear before the Medical Board at the University. Q17. What are the admission requirements for the category of religious minorities? A. They must be resident of Pakistan, belong to religious minorities and have passed HSC (Pre-Engineering/ Pre-Medical / Computer Science / Commerce / Arts /Arts-Math) Part I and II from any Board of Intermediate Education or Equivalent foreign examination as recognized by the University can apply
FAQ_extracted_chunk_8	FAQ_extracted	Faq	Pre-Medical / Computer Science / Commerce / Arts /Arts-Math) Part I and II from any Board of Intermediate Education or Equivalent foreign examination as recognized by the University can apply for the religious minorities category. Q18. Are DAE holders eligible to apply for the admissions? A. For admission in the category reserved for Diploma of Associate Engineer (DAE), the applicant must pass the qualifying examination from institution recognized by Sindh Board of Technical Education (SBTE), with minimum 60%, during last three years. Applicants who are awaiting the result are not eligible to apply. Entry Test Q1. What are the passing marks in Entry Tests? A. 50% marks in entry test are required to qualify for admission. Q2. When would the Entry test be held? A. Entry Test schedule will be available at www.neduet.edu.pk/admission. Q3. When would Entry Test result be announced? A. Pre-Admission Entry test result will be announced after the last session of the computer- based test and available on NEDUET website. Q4. How many times a candidate may appear in the entry test? A. Pre-Admission Entry test will be held twice. A candidate can appear in both tests. Separate fee for each test is required to pay. Q5.
FAQ_extracted_chunk_9	FAQ_extracted	Faq	appear in the entry test? A. Pre-Admission Entry test will be held twice. A candidate can appear in both tests. Separate fee for each test is required to pay. Q5. Which Pre-Admission Entry test score will be considered for the admission? A. Between the two results, whichever is higher will be considered for the admission. Q6. How much fee will be charged for the second attempt? A. The test fee for second attempt of entry test will be notified on NED website. Q7. What will be dates for the Pre-Admission Entry Phase-I and Phase-II? A. The test dates for both phases will be notified on NED website. Q8. What type of Pre-Admission Entry Test is taken at NED UET? A. Pre-Admission Entry Test is computer based and comprised of Multiple-Choice Questions (MCQs) with Four Sections. Each of 25 marks and comprising of the subjects based on applicant’s HSC or Equivalent examinations Group. Following table illustrates the sections of the test. Subjects in HSC/Equivalent Examinations Section in Pre-Admission Entry Test Pre-Engineering Group /DAE (Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry) Section 1 English Section 2 Mathematics Section 3 Physics Section 4 Chemistry Pre-Medical Group (Biology, Physics, Chemistry) Section 1 English Section 2 Biology Section 3
FAQ_extracted_chunk_10	FAQ_extracted	Faq	Group /DAE (Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry) Section 1 English Section 2 Mathematics Section 3 Physics Section 4 Chemistry Pre-Medical Group (Biology, Physics, Chemistry) Section 1 English Section 2 Biology Section 3 Physics Section 4 Chemistry Computer Science Group (Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science) Section 1 English Section 2 Mathematics Section 3 Physics Section 4 Computer Science Computer Science Group (Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science) Section 1 English Section 2 Mathematics Section 3 Statistics Section 4 Computer Science Commerce Group Section 1 English Section 2 Accounting Section 3 Economics Section 4 Business Mathematics Arts Group Section 1 English 1 Section 2 English 2 Section 3 Basic Mathematics Section 4 General Knowledge Arts (Mathematics) Group Section 1 English 1 Section 2 English 2 Section 3 Mathematics** Section 4 General Knowledge * *Mathematics -- equivalent to the HSC/GCE level Pre-Engineering Group Mathematics course content. Q8. Is there any weightage of entry test marks in merit score? A Yes, the weightage of test score is 60%. Admission Schedule Q1. When will the merit list be displayed? A. Please see “Admission Schedule” available at www.neduet.edu.pk/admission. Q2. What is the admission schedule? A. Admission Schedule is a document with important dates for admissions & related activities. Tuition / Semester
FAQ_extracted_chunk_11	FAQ_extracted	Faq	Please see “Admission Schedule” available at www.neduet.edu.pk/admission. Q2. What is the admission schedule? A. Admission Schedule is a document with important dates for admissions & related activities. Tuition / Semester Fee Q1. How much is the admission fee? A. Please see Chapter-8 of the Undergraduate Prospectus. Q2. When do I have to pay Self-Finance Fee? A. Self-Finance fee has to be paid latest by the due date of the submission of online application form. For any updates please visit NEDUET website. Q3. How much fees are charged against Self-Finance or Self Sponsor? A. Following are the fees: • Self-Finance Fee Rs. 890,000/- + 3% Tax* • Self-Finance (Sponsored Seats) Fee Rs. 1,100,000/- + 3% Tax* • Foreign Student Fee Rs. 1,100,000/- + 3% Tax* *as per the directive of Sindh Board of Revenue Q4. What if I will get admission in Regular scheme, would the self-finance amount be refunded? A. Yes, when you opt for admission in Regular Seat, total self-finance fee will be refunded. For refund you have to submit self-finance refund form (available at website) with all relevant documents as required. Q5. Does Self-finance fee include admission fee? A. No, it does not. Self-finance fee is to be
FAQ_extracted_chunk_12	FAQ_extracted	Faq	submit self-finance refund form (available at website) with all relevant documents as required. Q5. Does Self-finance fee include admission fee? A. No, it does not. Self-finance fee is to be paid once only at the time of admission form submission. You must have to pay admission fee at the time of admission in addition to the Self-Finance fee. Admission Requirements Q1. What documents are required during Medical Fitness Test? A. You are required to bring Admission form along with all the documents mentioned in the document’s checklist. Q2. Do I have to bring any other document on the Admission Day? A. No, you are required to bring Admission fee along with the required documents only. Q3. Can I pay the admission fee after taking the admission? A. No, your admission will not be confirmed until the admission fee is paid on the day of interview/admission. The admission fee may in the form of Cash or Pay order/Demand draft in favor of Director Finance, NEDUET. Q4. Can anyone having HSC or Equivalent examinations Pre-Medical, apply for only Bio- Engineering programme? A. Please refer to Chapter 4 and Chapter 5 of current Undergraduate Prospectus. Q5. Can anyone having passed HSC or Equivalent
FAQ_extracted_chunk_13	FAQ_extracted	Faq	Equivalent examinations Pre-Medical, apply for only Bio- Engineering programme? A. Please refer to Chapter 4 and Chapter 5 of current Undergraduate Prospectus. Q5. Can anyone having passed HSC or Equivalent examinations Commerce examination apply for admission? A. Yes, please refer to Chapter 4 and Chapter 5 of current Undergraduate Prospectus. Q6. Can anyone having passed HSC or Equivalent examinations (Science General/Computer Science) examination with Physics, Mathematics and Computer Science eligible for admission? A. Yes, please refer to Chapter 4 and Chapter 5 of current Undergraduate Prospectus. Miscellaneous Q1. Where Bachelor of Architecture and BS Development Studies classes are held? A. Classes of Bachelor of Architecture and BS Development Studies are held at City Campus which is adjacent to Govt. DJ Science College. Classes for Bio-Medical Engineering are held at LEJ Campus situated opposite to Liaquat National Hospital. Q2. Is there any Shuttle Bus Service available for City Campus and LEJ Campus? A. No, there is no specific bus service for these campuses. However, some of the shuttle buses pass in front of these campuses. Details will be provided on the day of orientation. Q3. What is the duration of degree programmes offered by the University? A. All programmes are of
FAQ_extracted_chunk_14	FAQ_extracted	Faq	front of these campuses. Details will be provided on the day of orientation. Q3. What is the duration of degree programmes offered by the University? A. All programmes are of Four years duration except Bachelors in Architecture which is of Five years duration. Note: For further queries please visit Helpdesk on your Admission Portal. University reserves the right to make any correction(s) / change(s) without notice.
