Prime Minister’s Youth Laptop Scheme (PMYLS) – Phase IV 
The students listed below who have not yet received their laptops under the Prime Minister's Youth 
Laptop Scheme (PMYLS) – Phase IV are hereby reminded for the final time to collect their laptops 
from the Department of Student Affairs on an immediate basis. 
Please note that any laptops remaining uncollected by Monday, 09 March 2026, will be returned to 
the Higher Education Commission (HEC) authorities. No claims or requests will be entertained after 
the deadline. 
Required Documents (Mandatory: Failure may result in non-issuance of the laptop) 
1. University ID Card (Original along with one photocopy) 
2. CNIC (Original along with one photocopy) 
3. One passport-size photograph 
4. Transcript / Academic record till Fall 2025 
 Only the concerned student is permitted to collect the laptop. Laptops will not be handed over 
to relatives or representatives. 
