foreign_students_admission_chunk_0	foreign_students_admission	Foreign Students Admission	ADMISSION OF FOREIGN STUDENTS ============================= 1. Foreign Students ------------------- The NED University does not entertain any admission request from Foreigners directly. Foreigners are admitted against reserved seats if their names are recommended by the Higher Education Commission of Pakistan (HEC) OR Economic Affairs Division (Ministry of Education, Government of Pakistan) (EAD). 2. Eligibility Criteria ----------------------- a. Pre-requisite Qualification - Higher Secondary Certificate (HSC) Pre-Engineering (Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics) - OR equivalent qualification with Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics - NED University does NOT accept any qualification without subjects Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics - Must have passed HSC Pre-Engineering with at least 60% aggregate marks b. Pre-Admission Entry Test - Must qualify the University's Pre-Admission Entry Test based on HSC level subjects: English, Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics - Foreigners and Overseas Pakistani candidates may take SAT examination instead of the entry test: * SAT I: minimum 800 score * SAT II: minimum 1500 score (in Physics, Chemistry and Mathematics) c. English Language Skill - Tested through the Pre-Admission Entry Test - Medium of instruction in all subjects is English 3. Facilities ------------- a. Residences On Campus (Hostel - local standard): -------------------------------------- Service Security Deposit Type Room Rent Charges (Refundable) ------- --------- -------
foreign_students_admission_chunk_1	foreign_students_admission	Foreign Students Admission	of instruction in all subjects is English 3. Facilities ------------- a. Residences On Campus (Hostel - local standard): -------------------------------------- Service Security Deposit Type Room Rent Charges (Refundable) ------- --------- ------- -------------- Cubicle Rs. 900/pm Rs. 900/pm Locals: Rs. 3,000 Foreigners: Rs. 15,000 Dormitory Rs. 700/pm - - Off-Campus: ----------- Two Bedroom flat: approximately Rs. 5,500 - Rs. 6,000 per month (Cost of living depends on individual's standard of living) b. Food - Canteen provides varieties of food on payment c. Laundry - On payment d. Medical Facilities - Free e. Security - NED University provides security on campus 4. Visa Processing ------------------ As NED University does not entertain any admission request from Foreigners directly, Foreigners are admitted against reserved seats only if their names are recommended by: - Higher Education Commission of Pakistan (HEC) - OR Economic Affairs Division (EAD), Ministry of Education, Government of Pakistan
GuideLines_extracted_chunk_0	GuideLines_extracted	Guidelines	On the last page, Transaction Slip will be generated, mentioning Transaction ID along with your information and the fees to be submitted in the designated commercial banks using this transaction slip. Same transaction ID can be used for multiple transactions. Guideline for UNDERGRADUATE ADMISSIONS Pre-Admission Entry Test 1. Register yourself in Admission Web Portal at NED University Website “www.neduet.edu.pk/admission” by entering your Name (as per Matriculation or equivalent certificate), Father’s name (as per Matriculation or equivalent certificate), e-Mail address (please ensure you have entered your active email address) and Date of Birth (as per Matriculation or equivalent certificate). 2. You will receive User ID and Password through email on the email provided in step 1. 3. Please log-in to Admission Web Portal using your user ID and Password provided through email. 4. Select the following: i. Board from where you passed HSC or equivalent examination. ii. Your HSC Examination group i.e. Pre-Engineering or Pre-Medical, etc. iii. Your Domicile. iv. Select category(ies) for which you are eligible to apply. v. Click on save and move to NEXT step. 5. Go to the subsequent pages of Online Admission Web Portal and complete all required information. 6. Please make sure to upload an
GuideLines_extracted_chunk_1	GuideLines_extracted	Guidelines	on save and move to NEXT step. 5. Go to the subsequent pages of Online Admission Web Portal and complete all required information. 6. Please make sure to upload an acceptable photograph of candidate as mentioned in “Guideline for the Online Application-Photograph”. 7. 8. Go to the designated banks’ branch as mentioned on the Transaction Slip. 9. Submit the fees as mentioned on the Transaction Slip. 10. Admit card will be available at the admission portal after confirmation of the fee submission by the bank (within 3 to 5 working days). Delay in issuance of admit card may be due to invalid/inappropriate photograph or non-confirmation of fee payment through online by the bank. In that case please write your query on Admission Helpdesk. 11. Don’t forget to bring the print out of your Pre-Admission Entry Test Admit Card at the day of Entry Test (mentioned in the schedule on admission website). After Qualifying the Pre-Entry Admission Test 12. Merit lists of different categories will be displayed on NED Website (www.neduet.edu.pk/admission) as per Admission Schedule. 13. If you are called in the Merit List, follow the schedule and perform the following activities. Note If your name appears in the Merit Lists
GuideLines_extracted_chunk_2	GuideLines_extracted	Guidelines	as per Admission Schedule. 13. If you are called in the Merit List, follow the schedule and perform the following activities. Note If your name appears in the Merit Lists 14. Print the filled Application Form from the Admission Web Portal. 15. Sign the Application Form. Also get your form duly signed by your Parents / Guardian and Oath Commissioner. 16. Signed Admission form, along with all documents mentioned in Document Checklist, are to be submitted at the time of interview as mentioned in the Admission Schedule on Admission Website. 17. Candidate will be called for Pre-Admission Interview as per Admission Schedule.  For any further queries, please read the Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) available on NED UET website.  For further queries please visit Helpdesk on your Admission Portal.  For admission in category for those having disability (excluding the disability of deadness, dumbness and blindness) and passed HSC (Pre-Engineering/Computer Science) part I and II (as the case may be), from any Board of Intermediate of Education situated in province of Sindh and having certificate of disability from Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities (DEPD), Government of Sindh. Further the candidate is required to appear before the Medical
GuideLines_extracted_chunk_3	GuideLines_extracted	Guidelines	province of Sindh and having certificate of disability from Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities (DEPD), Government of Sindh. Further the candidate is required to appear before the Medical Board at the University.  For admission in the category reserved for Diploma of Associate Engineer (DAE), the applicant must pass the qualifying examination from institution recognized by Sindh Board of Technical Education (SBTE), with minimum 60%, during last three years.
