hostel_facilities_chunk_0	hostel_facilities	Hostel Facilities	NED UNIVERSITY - HOSTEL FACILITIES ==================================== The University provides residential accommodation for outstation students through Muhammad Bin Qasim (MBQ) Hostel, located adjacent to the main campus. This facility consists of two separate blocks for boys (MBQ-I and MBQ-II) and a dedicated Girls Hostel. Accommodation is primarily reserved for students who are non-residents of Karachi and is allocated through a Hostel Allotment Committee appointed by the Vice-Chancellor. 1. HOSTEL INFRASTRUCTURE ------------------------- Hostel Type of Room No. of Rooms Room Size Capacity ------ ------------- ------------- ------------------- -------- MBQ-I Cubicle 16 12'x8'6" = 102 sq ft 16 students Dormitory 34 18'6"x11' = 203 sq ft MBQ-II Cubicle 48 12'x8'6" = 102 sq ft 48 students Dormitory 72 18'6"x11' = 203 sq ft Girls Hostel Dormitory 20 12'x16' = 192 sq ft 41 students 2. FACILITIES & SERVICES ------------------------- - Common Room - Prayer Hall - Warden's Office - Canteen service (hygienic meals and refreshments) - Wi-Fi connectivity throughout the hostel premises - Washing and laundry services - Hostel Management Information System (HMIS) for computerised records 3. ALLOTMENT PROCESS --------------------- Eligibility: - Students admitted from boards other than Karachi Basis: - Transparent and merit-based - First come, first served Timeline: - Applications invited in
hostel_facilities_chunk_1	hostel_facilities	Hostel Facilities	computerised records 3. ALLOTMENT PROCESS --------------------- Eligibility: - Students admitted from boards other than Karachi Basis: - Transparent and merit-based - First come, first served Timeline: - Applications invited in November from newly admitted first-year students (after completion of admission process) - Merit list maintained Room Assignment: - First-year students initially allotted in hostel halls - Shifted to rooms as they become available (according to merit) - Dormitories: 3 students per room (due to shortage) - Cubicle rooms: reserved for final-year students 4. ADDITIONAL NOTES -------------------- - Boarding (mess) facilities are NOT provided by the University (canteen service available within hostel premises) - Residents get Wi-Fi for online academic resources - Washing and laundry facilities available - All records computerised via Hostel Management Information System (HMIS) - Hostel charges collected in advance on a semester basis
