Parallel Processing Laboratory 
Thislaboratoryfulfills 
high 
performance computational needs of the 
department. At present Parallel Processing lab 
has latest servers, which act as ORACLE and 
OPNET servers. The lab also has a four-node 
(PIV) Beowulf cluster, connected via 100Mbbs 
Star topology which is used for high end 
computing. It is Linux based and uses "MPICH" 
as cluster management software. Moreover, 
the user and resource administration is being 
done 
using 
"OpenPBS". 
"NAS 
Parallel 
Benchmark" is also installed on this cluster.  
