16. 
 DEPARTMENT OF MATHEMATICS 
Department of Mathematics was 
established as an independent department in 
2010 to cater to the requirements of 
Mathematics 
and 
Statistics 
in 
all 
the 
disciplines. The aim of establishing an 
independent department was to initiate its 
own degree programs. This Department has 
launched a Master’s degree program in 
Applied Mathematics with the objective of 
imparting 
strong 
theoretical 
knowledge 
reinforced with skills in utilizing software tools 
for mathematical applications in different 
professions. The focus of the said program is 
related 
to 
the 
particular 
fields 
like 
Engineering, Computational and Financial 
mathematics. This program commenced from 
July 2011, and has now successfully running. 
Master in Applied Mathematics is 
beneficial to both engineering and science 
graduates. This program is initiated to 
encourage 
multi-disciplinary research be 
offering opportunities for higher studies to 
fresh graduates as well as experienced 
graduates employed in industry and other 
professional sectors, and to provide a route 
towards a Ph.D degree to those desiring to do 
so.  
16.1 
RESEARCH FACILITIES 
The Department has a well-equipped 
computer facility along with related software 
(like Matlab, Mathematica, SPSS, Minitab). 
16.2 
RESEARCH AREAS 
 
Applied Mathematics 
 
Computational Mathematics
