PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_0	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	Page 1 of 12 NED UNIVERSITY OF ENGINEERING & TECHNOLOGY E-MAIL: dracad@neduet.edu.pk | WEBSITE: http://www.neduet.edu.pk PHONE: (92-21) 99261261-8 EXT-2221/FAX: (92-21) 99261255 No.Acad/34(88)/8529 Dated: 22-01-2025 NOTIFICATION It is hereby notified that the University Syndicate vide its Resolution No. SYN-211.5(b) dated 23-12-2024 has approved changes/revision in PhD Regulations, as under: 1. TITLE AND NATURE OF DEGREE 1.1 These Regulations may be called the NED University of Engineering & Technology Regulations-2024 for the proposed Postgraduate studies leading to the Degree of Doctor of Philosophy. 2. COMMENCEMENT 2.1 These Regulations shall be applicable for Doctor of Philosophy students admitted in Fall 2024 session and onwards unless otherwise specified. 2.2 For the PhD Supervision requirement, clause 3.7.1 will be applicable to all existing and new PhD supervisors. 2.3 The grading scheme in 4.1(c) shall be applicable w.e.f Spring semester 2025. 2.4 For the PhD Research Proposal evaluation requirement, clause 4.5 will be applicable with immediate effect. 2.5 Clause 7.7(a) regarding AI generated component in Similarity Index will also be applicable with immediate effect. 3. CRITERIA AND PROCEDURE FOR ADMISSION 3.1 Minimum requirement for admission in the Programme shall be Master’s degree (minimum 18 year). The Master’s degree should be obtained after completion of minimum of
PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_1	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	AND PROCEDURE FOR ADMISSION 3.1 Minimum requirement for admission in the Programme shall be Master’s degree (minimum 18 year). The Master’s degree should be obtained after completion of minimum of 30 credit hours from an HEC-recognized university/DAI with minimum 3.0 CGPA (out of 4.0). (a) All applicants to PhD programmes shall be required to qualify (by securing a minimum of 60% score), one of the following non-subject specific admission tests (except of certain science disciplines where the University may decide for subject specific tests); (i) The Graduate Record Examination (GRE) test administered by the Education Testing Service; (ii) A graduate admission test administered by the Education Testing Council. (iii) An equivalent test developed by the University. (b) For those having completed Masters’ degree in a different discipline may be considered for admission provided that the Postgraduate Admissions Committee is satisfied that: (i) The individual has a strong interest in pursuing a PhD degree in the discipline he/she has applied for admission, and has passed GRE- Subject/ Equivalent Test (in case the GRE-Subject test for a specific field / discipline is not available / conducted in Pakistan) with minimum 50% marks in the discipline of admission, in addition to the General
PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_2	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	the GRE-Subject test for a specific field / discipline is not available / conducted in Pakistan) with minimum 50% marks in the discipline of admission, in addition to the General test mentioned in 3.1(a). Page 2 of 12 (ii) The applicant’s prior education has sufficiently prepared him or her to undertake the course of studies of the doctoral programme or the preparation can be deemed satisfactory by taking a few additional courses of 6 to 9 credit hours after starting the programme. (c) Those having obtained Master's degree from any foreign universities shall be required to submit an equivalence of the degree issued by the HEC to this effect. 3.2 In addition to the above mentioned requirements, the admission test shall fulfil the following requirements: 3.2.1 The validity of the tests result, mentioned above, shall be one year from the date of the test. 3.2.2 The test offered by the University, at par with GRE General Test, will be administered centrally by Admission Committee. 3.3 An application for admission to the Programme shall be submitted to the Chairperson of the concerned Department along with all required documents (including a statement of purpose and synopsis), indicating the proposed major subject area
PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_3	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	the Programme shall be submitted to the Chairperson of the concerned Department along with all required documents (including a statement of purpose and synopsis), indicating the proposed major subject area of research work. 3.4 At the time of application, the candidate must provide evidence of adequate financial support to undertake the complete PhD studies. 3.5 No Objection Certificate (NOC) from employer will be required at the time of application; if applicable. 3.6 A departmental Postgraduate Admission Committee shall be constituted by the concerned Dean which shall comprise of the Chairperson and two senior faculty members of the Department/Faculty. The Committee shall assess an applicant's suitability on the basis of the test mentioned in 3.2, Statement of Purpose, synopsis, academic and professional qualifications, professional experience, referees’ letters of recommendation, and shall submit recommendations to the concerned Dean to allow induction through concerned Chairperson. The Committee shall be notified by Registrar. 3.7.1 (a) The departmental Postgraduate Admission Committee, with the consent of the candidate and subsequent to the endorsement by the concerned Chairperson, will also recommend one supervisor for each candidate. In cases where essential, co-supervisor(s) shall be allowed. Their formal allocation shall be made at the time of admission of a
