PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_6	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	(iii). (vi) Foreign co-supervisor shall be evaluated based on the PhD degree and publication requirements for a specific PhD project only. The supervisor shall provide evidence of HEC recognition of the university where the foreign co-supervisor had graduated from. (vii) Supervisor / co-supervisor with a valid HEC Approved PhD Supervisor status shall be exempted from fulfilling the clauses 3.7.1(b)(i) to 3.7.1(b)(iii) till the expiry of their award letters. (viii) Supervisor(s) / co-supervisor(s), who are currently supervising PhD scholars but their HEC Approved PhD Supervisor status has been expired, shall also be required to fulfil clauses 3.7.1(b)(i) to 3.7.1(b)(iii) with immediate effect. (ix) The supervisor / co-supervisor shall be exempted from fulfilling 3.7.1(b)(iii) if (s)he has previously been issued HEC Approved PhD Supervisor letter. (c) In addition to fulfilling Approved PhD Supervisor criteria as per 3.7.1(b), the supervisor / co-supervisor shall fulfill the following conditions for every research project: (i) The supervisor shall be a faculty member of this University. (ii) Co-supervisor shall be a faculty member or researcher of this University or any other public or private university or DAI, or a researcher or scientist at any R&D or public / private sector organization. (iii) Co-supervisor, from outside NED University
