PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_10	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	shall decide such cases. (iii) A residency requirement for a period of at least two years shall be mandatory. 4.1(b) (i) The scholar is required to successfully pass these courses within minimum twelve- month period (if the scholar has to pass 18 credit hours coursework) and minimum eighteen months period (if the scholar has to pass additional 6 to 9 credit hours coursework). This period can be extended by a further six months with approval of concerned Dean on the recommendations of Supervisor and Chairperson. 4.1(b) (ii) Courses up to a maximum of 9 credit hours shall be allowed in a semester. 4.1(b)(iii) In special circumstances, University may grant extension for Coursework, Comprehensive Examination and Research Proposal defense till Third year / Sixth semester from the date of admission in the Programme, including all withdrawals, beyond which the admission shall be cancelled. 4.1 (c) The following grades/grade points with the equivalent marks shall be awarded to the students on the basis of their performance in each course of study. Page 5 of 12 Grade Grade Point Existing Marks Proposed Marks Proposed Remarks A 4.0 88 – 100 85 - 100 Excellent A – 3.7 80 – 87 80 – 84
