PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_13	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	Any student who is unable to continue PhD while being at the stage of course work or beyond, may seek for either of the following: (a) Request for cancellation of admission without being awarded any degree or certificate. (b) Request consideration for the award of Masters’ Degree provided all relevant Masters’ Degree regulations are applied. 4.3 Comprehensive Examination shall comprise of written examination (and oral if deemed significant by the Committee), covering at least the knowledge imparted in all assigned courses completed during induction period. Page 6 of 12 4.4 During the induction period the scholar shall have to prepare a research proposal, which the scholar shall be required to present in a Seminar after obtaining PhD Candidacy. If the Supervisor/Department deems that the proposal needs further work, it may apprise the scholar appropriately assigning him a timeline for a proposal re-defense. 4.5 Subsequent to the presentation in Research Seminar, the proposal shall be forwarded by the Supervisor to the concerned Board of Studies on the prescribed format approved by ASRB. (a) The concerned Board of Studies may adopt its own procedure for evaluating the technical and financial merit of the proposal and will submit, along with the proposal, its
PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_14	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	ASRB. (a) The concerned Board of Studies may adopt its own procedure for evaluating the technical and financial merit of the proposal and will submit, along with the proposal, its recommendations on prescribed format duly endorsed by the Chairperson. (b) After the consideration of the Research Proposal by the respective Board of Studies, the Chairperson will send it to the concerned Dean, who will subsequently forward the same to the following reviewers: i. One reviewer from abroad. ii. One reviewer from any HEI or research institute within Country. (c) Both the reviewers may be from outside the Country, in case of non- availability of a reviewer from within the country. (d) The reviewer should be a full time PhD faculty member at any university, or a researcher or scientist at any R&D or public/private sector organization. (e) The reviewer should not have been associated with the candidate’s PhD research work (other than usual contact in taught courses or other non-thesis activities within the University), nor he / she be related to the candidate or Supervisor(s). (f) The reviewer from outside the Country should belong to a university ranked among the world top 500 universities by the Times Higher Education or
PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted_chunk_15	PhD_Regulations_23_12_2024_extracted	Phd Regulations 23 12 2024	to the candidate or Supervisor(s). (f) The reviewer from outside the Country should belong to a university ranked among the world top 500 universities by the Times Higher Education or QS World Ranking in the year corresponding to research proposal evaluation year. (g) The reviewer from within the Country should have least 10 research publications in the subject area of PhD project in peer-reviewed journals of international repute as determined by the University. S(He) should be an active researcher. (h) The reviewers as proposed by the concerned Dean and approved by the Vice Chancellor will be accordingly notified. (i) After receiving the reviewers’ comments, the following actions will be taken; i. In case the two reviewers recommend minor changes, the Supervisor shall forward the Research Proposal to ASRB along with the reviewers’ reports, affirming that the PhD Scholar has incorporated the suggestions. ii. In case, if any reviewer recommends major changes, the research proposal shall be revised/modified according to the suggestions received from the reviewer(s) and then resubmitted to the reviewers for their consent. The revised research proposal shall subsequently be forwarded to ASRB along with the reviewers’ reports for inclusion in the ASRB meeting via concerned Dean. Page 7
