SECTION IV (ACCOUNTING) - (For Commerce Group) 
1. Which of the following equations properly represents a derivation of the fundamental 
accounting equation? 
(A) Assets + liabilities = owner's equity. (B) Assets = owner's equity 
(C) cash = assets. 
(D) Assets - liabilities = owner's equity. 
