university_history_chunk_0	university_history	University History	NED UNIVERSITY - HISTORY & BACKGROUND ====================================== 1. ESTABLISHMENT ----------------- The NED University of Engineering & Technology was established in March 1977 under an act of the Provincial Assembly of Sindh, after upgrading the former NED Government Engineering College, which was set up in 1921. It is one of the oldest institutions in Pakistan for teaching and producing Engineering graduates. 2. HISTORICAL TIMELINE ----------------------- 1921 (Aug 29): - College Principal C.S. Shahani pushed to start Engineering Degree classes to meet Civil Engineer demand for the Sukkur Barrage project - Application made to the University of Bombay through the Commissioner of Sindh - Bombay University rejected it (insufficient finance, needed separate buildings and labs) Funding: - Donations from Puribai and Becharbai Trust - Vishandas Fatehchand Brothers - Rs. 150,000 from the family of Nadirshaw Edulji Dinshaw (a massive donation for that time) 1922: - 78 students provisionally admitted into first-year classes 1923 (May 23): - NED College provisionally granted affiliation by University of Bombay for first and second year Civil Engineering courses - Originally named "Prince of Wales Engineering College" - Later renamed in memory of Nadirshaw Edulji Dinshaw (NED) 1923 (Jul 1): - Mr. G.N. Gokhale joined as first full-time
university_history_chunk_1	university_history	University History	courses - Originally named "Prince of Wales Engineering College" - Later renamed in memory of Nadirshaw Edulji Dinshaw (NED) 1923 (Jul 1): - Mr. G.N. Gokhale joined as first full-time Principal - Prior: Rai Sahib Bhupatrai acted as Honorary Principal - Mr. S.B. Jannarkar: first Professor and Vice Principal 1927 (Feb): - Permanent affiliation granted 1922-1947: - Affiliated to the University of Bombay 1947: - Taken over by the Government of Sindh - Renamed: NED Government Engineering College - Affiliated to the University of Sindh 1951: - Affiliation transferred to the University of Karachi 1964: - Plan to shift from congested downtown area to a new site adjoining the University of Karachi - World Bank assistance: Rs. 118 million (two phases) 1975: - College shifted to new 40-hectare Main Campus 1977 (Mar 1): - Became NED University of Engineering & Technology 3. ORIGINAL BUILDINGS ---------------------- Four blocks and two sheds: - Main Block: Seth Fatehchand Dewandas Khilnani Hall - Power House, Electrical & Hydraulics Labs, Workshops: named after Bai Puribai and Bacharbai - Fourth block (1945): Classroom, Clerk's Office, Civil Drawing Hall - Shed 1: Carpentry and Smithy Shops - Shed 2: Electrical Lab and Engine Room (technician training) Cost:
university_history_chunk_2	university_history	University History	and Bacharbai - Fourth block (1945): Classroom, Clerk's Office, Civil Drawing Hall - Shed 1: Carpentry and Smithy Shops - Shed 2: Electrical Lab and Engine Room (technician training) Cost: - Buildings: just over Rs. 265,000 - Equipment, books, furniture: just under Rs. 400,000 4. GROWTH ---------- - 1923: 50 students enrolled - Present: ~11,986 students (UG and PG) - Bio-Medical Engineering at LEJ Campus (land & building worth Rs. 350 million donated by Late Latif Ebrahim Jamal) 5. TIEST - THAR INSTITUTE OF ENGINEERING, SCIENCES & TECHNOLOGY ----------------------------------------------------------------- - Established: October 2019 - Location: Mithi, district Tharparkar, Sindh (~350 km East of Karachi) - Purpose: Quality education for deprived students in the area; produce workforce for coal excavation and power generation industries - Programmes launched: - BS Computer Science (2019) - Civil Engineering (2021) - Mechanical, Electrical, Chemical, Mining Engineering (upcoming) 6. VICE CHANCELLORS (Chronological Order) ------------------------------------------- 1. Mr. A. M. Akhoond 2. Prof. Dr. A. T. Khan 3. Prof. Dr. Jameel Ahmed Khan 4. Prof. Dr. M. Munir Hasan 5. Prof. Dr. A. Q. Qazi 6. Engr. Abul Kalam 7. Prof. Dr. M. Afzal Haque 8. Dr. Sarosh Hashmat Lodi 9. Prof. Dr. Noman Ahmed 10. Prof. Dr.
university_history_chunk_3	university_history	University History	Hasan 5. Prof. Dr. A. Q. Qazi 6. Engr. Abul Kalam 7. Prof. Dr. M. Afzal Haque 8. Dr. Sarosh Hashmat Lodi 9. Prof. Dr. Noman Ahmed 10. Prof. Dr. Muhammad Tufail (present VC)
vc_message_chunk_0	vc_message	Vc Message	VICE CHANCELLOR'S MESSAGE ========================== "100 Years of Excellence in Engineering Education" With heartfelt gratitude to Allah Almighty, I am truly honored and privileged to serve as the Vice-Chancellor of this esteemed institution—NED University of Engineering and Technology—which stands as a distinguished symbol of resilience, innovation, and national service. As we proudly celebrate a century of transformative impact, the University reflects a legacy built upon academic rigor, societal contribution, and a deep commitment to engineering excellence. ACADEMIC PORTFOLIO ------------------- - 107 degree programmes (including 35 undergraduate offerings) - ~13,000 students - Graduates equipped with theoretical knowledge, creativity, analytical acumen, and practical expertise FACULTY -------- - Exceptional, diverse, and dedicated - Many hold doctoral degrees from renowned international institutions NATIONAL CENTERS OF EXCELLENCE ------------------------------- - National Incubation Center - National Centre for Cloud Computing and Data Analytics - National Center for Artificial Intelligence (NCAI) - National Center for Cybersecurity (NCCS) - National Center for Robotics and Automation (NCRA) CAMPUSES --------- - Main Campus (University Road) - Latif Ebrahim Jamal (LEJ) Campus (Stadium Road) - City Campus (Maulana Din Muhammad Wafai Road) - Thar Institute of Engineering, Sciences and Technology (TIEST) in Tharparkar (regional outreach for underserved communities) VISION ------- - Education beyond
vc_message_chunk_1	vc_message	Vc Message	Road) - City Campus (Maulana Din Muhammad Wafai Road) - Thar Institute of Engineering, Sciences and Technology (TIEST) in Tharparkar (regional outreach for underserved communities) VISION ------- - Education beyond technical instruction - Socially responsible, ethically grounded, forward-thinking professionals - Critical thinking, leadership, communication, problem-solving - Interdisciplinary learning, entrepreneurial spirit, engagement with real-world challenges ALUMNI ------- - Cornerstone of NED's enduring influence - Leadership positions in engineering, academia, business, government - Entrepreneurs driving innovation and employment - Spanning continents and industries CLOSING -------- As we celebrate 100 years of progress, we also embrace the challenges and possibilities of the future. With renewed determination, NED University is poised to lead national transformation—advancing research, fostering sustainable innovation, and expanding its impact. Guided by integrity, inclusivity, and excellence, we move forward to shape a future where education becomes the catalyst for meaningful change and national development. Prof. Dr. Muhammad Tufail Vice-Chancellor
